summary.text: McLoughlin House National Historic Site Act - Authorizes the Secretary of the Interior to acquire the McLoughlin House National Historic Site, Oregon City, Oregon, from willing sellers by donation, purchase, or exchange (except that lands or interests owned by Oregon City may be acquired by donation only). Requires that the acquired property be included within the boundaries and administered as part of the Fort Vancouver National Historic Site.

(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced in the House on February 12, 2003. The summary of that version is repeated here.)

McLoughlin House National Historic Site Act - Authorizes the Secretary of the Interior to acquire the McLoughlin House National Historic Site, Oregon City, Oregon, from willing sellers by donation, purchase, or exchange (except that lands or interests owned by Oregon City may be acquired by donation only). Requires that the acquired property be included within the boundaries and administered as part of the Fort Vancouver National Historic Site.

McLoughlin House Addition to Fort Vancouver National Historic Site Act - Authorizes the Secretary of the Interior to acquire the McLoughlin House (the McLoughlin House National Historic Site, including the Barclay House and other associated property and improvements), Oregon City, Oregon, from willing sellers by donation, purchase, or exchange (except that lands or interests owned by Oregon City may be acquired by donation only). Requires that the acquired property be included within the boundaries and administered as part of the Fort Vancouver National Historic Site.

Directs the Secretary to rename McLoughlin House National Historic Site as McLoughlin House.

(This measure has not been amended since it was reported to the Senate on June 9, 2003. The summary of that version is repeated here.)

McLoughlin House Addition to Fort Vancouver National Historic Site Act - Authorizes the Secretary of the Interior to acquire the McLoughlin House (the McLoughlin House National Historic Site, including the Barclay House and other associated property and improvements) Oregon City, Oregon, from willing sellers by donation, purchase, or exchange (except that lands or interests owned by Oregon City may be acquired by donation only). Requires that the acquired property be included within the boundaries and administered as part of the Fort Vancouver National Historic Site.

Directs the Secretary to rename McLoughlin House National Historic Site as McLoughlin House.

(This measure has not been amended since it was reported to the Senate on June 9, 2003. The summary of that version is repeated here.)

McLoughlin House Addition to Fort Vancouver National Historic Site Act - Authorizes the Secretary of the Interior to acquire the McLoughlin House (the McLoughlin House National Historic Site, including the Barclay House and other associated property and improvements) Oregon City, Oregon, from willing sellers by donation, purchase, or exchange (except that lands or interests owned by Oregon City may be acquired by donation only). Requires that the acquired property be included within the boundaries and administered as part of the Fort Vancouver National Historic Site.

Directs the Secretary to rename McLoughlin House National Historic Site as McLoughlin House.

dublinCore.dc:description: This file contains bill summaries and statuses for federal legislation. A bill summary describes the most significant provisions of a piece of legislation and details the effects the legislative text may have on current law and federal programs. Bill summaries are authored by the Congressional Research Service (CRS) of the Library of Congress. As stated in Public Law 91-510 (2 USC 166 (d)(6)), one of the duties of CRS is "to prepare summaries and digests of bills and resolutions of a public general nature introduced in the Senate or House of Representatives". For more information, refer to the User Guide that accompanies this file.
